 from the ruins. These stories explore fault lines between “rural” and “urban,” “backwardness” and “development,” and “before” and “after,” shedding light on the role of environmental forces in the history of human habitats.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCity planningzItalyzMessina. 0aCity planningzItaly. 0aEarthquake engineeringzItalyzBelice River Valley. 0aEarthquake engineeringzItalyzMessina. 0aEarthquake resistant designzItalyzBelice River Valley. 0aEarthquake resistant designzItalyzMessina. 0aEarthquakeszItalyzBelice River ValleyxHistoryy20th century. 0aEarthquakeszItalyzMessinaxHistoryy20th century. 7aNATURE / Earthquakes & Volcanoes.2bisacsh  abelice valley.  acatastrophe.  adestruction.  aearthquakes.  aengaging.  aenvironmental forces.  aenvironmental history.  afault lines.  ageology.  agovernment and governing.  ahistoriographical references.  ahuman habitats.  ainnovative study.  aitalian history.  aitaly.  amessina.  anatural disasters.  aphenomenon.  apolitics.  ascience.  ascientists.  aseismic events.  aseismology.  asicily.  asocial sciences.  astudy of disasters.  atectonic plates.  atheoretical.  atragedy.  aurban planning.  aurbanism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782389514?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782389514423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782389514/original  a978-3-11-099823-8  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME 